Measures Calculated from Shape File

Polsby-Popper

The Polsby-Popper (\(PP\)) measure is the ratio of the area of the district (\(A_{D}\)) to the area of a circle whose circumfrence is equal to the perimter (\(P_{D}\)) of the district.

\[ PP = 4\pi \times\frac{A_{D}}{P_{D}^2} \]

Schwartzberg

The Schwartzberg score (\(S\)) is the ratio of the perimter of the district (\(P_{D}\)) to the circumfrence of a circle whose area is equal to the area of the district.

\[ S = \frac{1}{P_D/C}=\frac{1}{P_D/(2\pi\sqrt{A_D/\pi})} \]

Reock Score

The Reock Score (R) is a measure of the area of the district \(A_D\) ratio of the district to the area of a minimum bounding cirle (\(A_{MBC}\)) that encloses the districts geometry.

\[ R = \frac{A_{D}}{A_{MBC}} \]
